Name: autosomal dominant cutis laxa 1
Definition: An autosomal dominant cutis laxa that has_material_basis_in heterozygous mutations in the ELN gene on chromosome 7q11.

Name: autosomal dominant cutis laxa 3
Definition: An autosomal dominant cutis laxa characterized by thin skin with visible veins and wrinkles

Name: autosomal dominant cutis laxa 2
Definition: An autosomal dominant cutis laxa that has_material_basis_in heterozygous mutation in the FBLN5 gene on chromosome 14q32.
